related_items.title: World War II material related to Gen. Carl Spaatz, mainly in North Africa
description: ca. 219 photographic prints (1 color) | Photographs show ceremonies transferring the air base at Casablanca, Morocco, to the United States; Spaatz meeting with Arthur Tedder (Gen. Dwight D. Eisenhower's deputy Supreme Allied Commander); gliders; views of Constantine, Algeria, and nearby Flying Fortresses in flight; etc. Mostly informal portraits. Also, Gen. Henry Harley Arnold at Casablanca Conference (Jan. 1943); group visiting the Arch of Triumph in Paris, France; aerial photograph of contrails from dog fight (2 Nov. 1944).

related_items.title: [Plan of the town and harbor of Tripoli]
description: Relief shown pictorially. Depths shown by fathoms. Sketch map showing the positions of the labeled vessels of the United States squadron. Pen-and-ink and watercolor on 3 sheets pasted together, sectioned in 3 and mounted on cloth. Title supplied by cataloger. Available also through the Library of Congress Web site as a raster image. Includes explanatory list of "References" and an inset of "A view of Tripoli in Barbary." Imperfect: Stained, mounted on cloth, losses and discoloration along the margins.
